The '''American Respiratory Care Foundation''' is a non-profit organization founded by the [[American Association for Respiratory Care]]<ref>American Respiratory Care Foundation http://www.arcfoundation.org/</ref> formed to provide funding for research in the field of [[pulmonology]] and [[respiratory care]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ersj.org.uk/content/9/3/393.full.pdf |title=Shneerson, JM The changing role of mechanical ventilation in COPD. Eur Respir J 1996;9,393-398 |format=PDF |date= |accessdate=2011-10-26}}</ref>  Formed in 1974 as the American Respiratory Therapy Foundation and then changed to the American Respiratory Care Foundation in 1986.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aarc.org/member_services/timeline/ |title=AARC Timeline |publisher=Aarc.org |date= |accessdate=2011-10-26}}</ref>  The ARCF is a partner with the United States [[Environmental Protection Agency]], who has awarded grants to the ARCF in order to help fund research directly related to [[asthma]] and asthma education.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.epa.gov/asthma/partners.html#National_Organizations |title=Federal Partners and Contacts &#124; Asthma &#124; US [[Environmental Protection Agency]] |publisher=Epa.gov |date=2010-11-17 |accessdate=2011-10-26}}</ref>

